abstract: Polls close at 7 p.m. Eastern time in most of the state, although the bulk of results will not be reported until after 8 p.m. In the meantime, there should be some demographic insights available from exit polls as well as a few statistical findings that we have to share with you.
lead_paragraph: Welcome to FiveThirtyEight's live blog of the New Hampshire primary. Polls have closed, and The New York Times has projected Mitt Romney as the winner, but we will still have plenty of statistical insights into the election.

headline.main: Analysis From the New Hampshire Primary
